    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1000"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1000">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.731/344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Göteborg</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sauer</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1000fn1">The same to the Minister in the
                        Netherlands, No. 112, February 26 (File No. 199.1/104).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your despatch 83. You may transmit private commercial cables when no other means
                    available for forwarding, assuming no responsibility for delivery. Such cables
                    must be strictly neutral; not relate to contraband or transfer of funds to
                    belligerents; should be in plain language not cipher and sufficiently clear on
                    face to be readily understood. Cost should be collected in advance from
                    sender.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BWJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
